classitems.description:
Show a notification on the dashboard.  Notifications typically show up as toaster message somewhere on the dashboard, 
but the dashboard reserves the right to format or even suppress these messages as suits its needs.

props.name: err
props.description: Error object if there was an error.

Send a "heartbeat" to the system, authorizing continued manual movement.  Manual moves must be continually
refreshed with this heartbeat function, or the tool will stop moving.

props.name: err
props.description: Error object if there was an error.

classitems.description:
Request a status report from the system.  The status object is returned in the callback to this function, as well as posted
with the status event.  To recieve updates to system status as it changes, you should bind a handler to the status event,
and _not_ poll using `requestStatus`.
classitems.name: requestStatus

props.description: The status report object

props.name: state
props.description: The system state, one of `idle`,`running`,`paused`,`stopped`,`manual` or `dead`

classitems.description:
Get the configuration object for the currently running app.  The configuration object is a JSON object 
of no specific description that is saved with each app.  It can be used to store app-specific configuration data.
classitems.name: getAppConfig

props.name: err
props.description: Error object if there was an error.

props.name: config
props.description: Configuration object or {} if no configuration has been saved in the app.

classitems.description: Set the app configuration to the provided option.
classitems.name: setAppConfig

params.name: config
params.description: The configuration object to set.

props.name: err
props.description: Error object if there was an error.

props.name: config
props.description: Configuration object or {} if no configuration has been saved in the app.

classitems.description: Get the current FabMo version
classitems.name: getVersion

props.name: err
props.description: Error object if there was an error.

props.name: version
props.description: Object describing the fabmo software version.

props.name: hash
props.description: The git hash of the currently running FabMo software

props.name: number
props.description: The user-friendly release version number (or empty string if not a released version

props.name: debug
props.description: True if FabMo is running in "debug mode"

props.name: type
props.description: The type of FabMo software build.  `dev` for development or `release` for released build.

classitems.description:
Control top level navigation for the dashboard.  Usually this is used to open another browser/tab window with a link from within an app,
or more rarely, to navigate away from the dashboard.
classitems.name: navigate

params.name: url
params.description: The URL to open

params.name: options
params.description: Options for top-level navigation.

props.name: target
props.description: The link target (same as the target argument of `window.open`)
